    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="450"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Allen</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Seoul, Korea</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 681.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>:</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>Mr. Hayashi, the Japanese minister, during his call on yesterday afternoon handed
                    me a translation of the new agreement with Korea, a copy of which I
                        inclosed.<note n="a" xml:id="d450fna">Agreement printed under Japan, <ref
                            target="#pg_437">page 437</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horace N. Allen</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
